Create a virtual environment
    python3 -m venv .venv
    Creates an isolated Python environment for the project.

Activate the virtual environment (macOS/Linux)
    source .venv/bin/activate
    Enables the venv so python/pip use project-local packages.

Install dependencies
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    Installs all packages required by the app.

Show installed packages
    pip list
    Quick check of what’s installed in your current environment.

Create new migrations
    python manage.py makemigrations
    Generates migration files from model changes.

Apply migrations to DB
    python manage.py migrate
    Applies pending migrations (schema updates).

Show migration status
    python manage.py showmigrations
    Lists migrations and whether each is applied.

Start development server
    python manage.py runserver
    Starts local dev server (default 127.0.0.1:8001).

Start server on custom host/port
    python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8001
    Useful for Docker/VM or alternate port testing.

Create admin/superuser
    python manage.py createsuperuser
    Creates login for Django admin.

Open Django shell
    python manage.py shell
    Interactive Python shell with Django context loaded.

Collect static files
    python manage.py collectstatic
    Gathers static assets for production serving.

Run project checks
    python manage.py check
    Runs Django system checks for config/model issues.

Run tests
    python manage.py test
    Executes Django test suite.

Dump and load DB data (fixtures)
    python manage.py dumpdata > data.json
    python manage.py loaddata data.json
    Export/import DB data for backup/dev seeding.

